1
00:00:39,957 --> 00:00:44,962
SURELY TOMORROW

2
00:00:47,047 --> 00:00:50,342
EMERGENCY

3
00:00:51,343 --> 00:00:53,220
Ji-woo…

4
00:01:21,624 --> 00:01:24,168
Hey, are you awake?

5
00:01:25,461 --> 00:01:26,670
What am I doing here?

6
00:01:26,754 --> 00:01:28,088
Why…

7
00:01:29,381 --> 00:01:31,258
Why did you do that?

8
00:01:31,842 --> 00:01:34,762
Se-yeong, what are you doing here?

9
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:37,932
Why are we…

10
00:01:38,015 --> 00:01:39,809
Kyeong-do carried you here.

11
00:01:45,314 --> 00:01:46,315
Ji-woo,

12
00:01:47,316 --> 00:01:50,069
I have to go because Dong-won has a fever.

13
00:01:50,735 --> 00:01:53,906
But Kyeong-do is here,
so make sure to get treated, okay?

14
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:56,200
Sorry, Se-yeong. You should get going.

15
00:01:56,283 --> 00:01:58,577
No need to say sorry.

16
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,123
My head is pounding.

17
00:02:08,419 --> 00:02:09,755
Drop me off here.

18
00:02:13,008 --> 00:02:14,426
Are you sure you can walk?

19
00:02:14,510 --> 00:02:15,386
Yes.

20
00:02:18,138 --> 00:02:19,014
Hey, Seo Ji-woo.

21
00:02:24,937 --> 00:02:28,649
Why would you take pills with alcohol?
What were you thinking?

22
00:02:29,733 --> 00:02:32,152
If it weren't for Se-yeong,
you could've been gone.

23
00:02:32,236 --> 00:02:34,530
Did your decibel rise as you got older?

24
00:02:38,784 --> 00:02:41,787
Fine. Then those pills.
Why did you take them?

25
00:02:43,956 --> 00:02:45,541
Because my mom came by.

26
00:02:46,292 --> 00:02:49,211
And I really don't like her.
She pissed me off.

27
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:53,924
Our mom is not a good mom.

28
00:02:54,008 --> 00:02:56,260
I didn't take them to die,
so don't overreact.

29
00:02:58,512 --> 00:02:59,513
Overreact?

30
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:03,767
Sure, I overreacted
and ran with you on my back.

31
00:03:03,851 --> 00:03:07,313
I couldn't sleep.
Not even with the sleeping pill.

32
00:03:07,396 --> 00:03:10,024
So I took another one,
but I still couldn't sleep.

33
00:03:11,525 --> 00:03:13,360
That's what happened.

34
00:03:13,986 --> 00:03:16,113
Is it true?
You did that just because you were drunk?

35
00:03:16,196 --> 00:03:18,908
How many times do I have to say it,
damn Lee Kyeong-do?

36
00:03:19,909 --> 00:03:22,536
I'm already out of energy as it is.
Stop roasting me.

37
00:03:25,414 --> 00:03:29,126
"Damn Lee Kyeong-do," wasting your time.
What the hell did I do that for?

38
00:03:32,212 --> 00:03:33,297
Go.

39
00:04:13,295 --> 00:04:14,672
Fucking lunatic.

40
00:04:26,016 --> 00:04:27,017
Hey.

41
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:33,107
Hey.

42
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:35,401
Overdosing on sleeping pills
after drinking?

43
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:37,945
You want everyone to know?
Should I write an article?

44
00:04:38,028 --> 00:04:39,321
Now be quiet and listen.

45
00:04:41,323 --> 00:04:43,826
When humans drink alcohol,
they become idiots.

46
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:45,953
It's okay if you know when to stop.

47
00:04:46,036 --> 00:04:50,290
But some don't know when to stop.
Like Seo Ji-woo and Lee Kyeong-do.

48
00:04:52,376 --> 00:04:56,296
That weed party in 2018,
why do you think you went there?

49
00:04:56,380 --> 00:05:00,884
You don't even smoke. Huh? You got drunk,
and you didn't know where you ended up.

50
00:05:00,968 --> 00:05:04,096
Imagine being a smoker.
Then you would've been in real trouble.

51
00:05:04,179 --> 00:05:06,056
You won't drink when there's no more left.

52
00:05:07,558 --> 00:05:12,354
You were a lunatic not to have realized
how many sleeping pills you were taking.

53
00:05:12,438 --> 00:05:14,231
Do you collect my articles?

54
00:05:14,815 --> 00:05:19,111
What about the gum on the way
to the fashion show? How do you know?

55
00:05:19,194 --> 00:05:22,448
I dare you to buy alcohol again.
I'll come back and throw everything out.

56
00:05:22,531 --> 00:05:25,075
Who are you? Who do you think you are?

57
00:05:25,159 --> 00:05:27,911
What else? It's humanity.

58
00:05:32,457 --> 00:05:34,001
Get out.

59
00:05:34,084 --> 00:05:37,504
Whether I drink or take pills,
mind your own business.

60
00:05:37,588 --> 00:05:40,299
So stop drinking already!

61
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:02,905
I know it's tough.

62
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:05,032
I know it best.

63
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:08,660
Still, you shouldn't drink anymore.

64
00:06:10,037 --> 00:06:14,249
That's, you know, extremely tough.

65
00:06:15,167 --> 00:06:17,711
It's better to make an effort
sooner rather than later. Okay?

66
00:06:19,838 --> 00:06:23,175
Okay. I hear you.

67
00:06:26,470 --> 00:06:27,471
Leave now, will you?

68
00:06:30,808 --> 00:06:32,976
Sleep tight and order some porridge.

69
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,479
You had your stomach pumped, so go easy.

70
00:06:37,231 --> 00:06:38,690
I'm sick of this.

71
00:06:39,191 --> 00:06:42,486
I heard you, so get out.
You're making me sober.

72
00:06:46,824 --> 00:06:49,534
Make sure to order porridge, okay?

73
00:07:02,381 --> 00:07:03,632
SURELY TOMORROW

74
00:07:03,715 --> 00:07:05,259
EPISODE 4

75
00:07:06,385 --> 00:07:08,554
See? I told you it'd look good on you.

76
00:07:08,637 --> 00:07:09,596
SPRING, 2007

77
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,098
Everything looks good on me.

78
00:07:11,974 --> 00:07:16,562
